          SORTED OUT YET!

       @{"GETFILE_ReadOnly" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/getfile.h/File" 99} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
          If @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}, a read-only recessed button gadget is used to present the
          file/drawer information. If @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}, an editable string gadget is used.
          The gadget will send the supported attributes in a @{"OM_NOTIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 69} when a
          this tag is @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98} and the user is finished editing the content of the
          string gadget. The application can be aware of all changes to the
          string gadget by setting @{"ICA_TARGET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/icclass.h/File" 27} to TARGET_IDCMP for this
          getfile gadget instance and watching @{"IDCMP_IDCMPUPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 856} messages.
          See the provided example program for an example on how this can be
          done.

          Defaults to @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}).

